      "source_url": "https://thaqalayn.net/hadith/34/2/11/26",
      "text": [
        " أَهْلِهِ قَالَ \"إِنْ رَغِبَ فِي اَلرِّبْحِ فَلْيُوجِبِ اَلثَّوْبَ عَلَى نَفْسِهِ وَ لاَ يَجْعَلْ فِي نَفْسِهِ أَنْ يَرُدَّ اَلثَّوْبَ عَلَى صَاحِبِهِ إِنْ رُدَّ عَلَيْهِ\"."
      ],
      "translations": {
        "en.bab-ul-qaim-publications": [
          "Hadith.3797 - Hammad narrated from Al-Halabi, who reported from Abu Abdullah (as):\nHe was asked about a man who buys a garment from the market for his family and takes it with a condition that he may return it if not accepted, but he is offered a profit if his family keeps it.\nImam (as) said: \"If he desires the profit, then he must make the garment binding upon himself (as a confirmed purchase) and should not intend in his heart to return the garment to its owner if it is returned to him.\""
        ]
      }
    },
